ory, hagiography, charter materials) for a specific time and purpose, frequently as a response to or intended resolution of internal or external crises. The book also discusses how the circumstances which triggered narrative production had an impact not only on the content but also on the form of the texts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBenedictine monasterieszFlandersxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval History. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184615392140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846153921423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846153921/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles